                        "content": "Etymology tree\nOld Persian 𐎱𐎠𐎼𐎿 (p-a-r-s /⁠pārs⁠/)\nMiddle Persian pʾls (/⁠pārs⁠/)\nMiddle Persian -yk' (/⁠-īg⁠/)\nMiddle Persian pʾlsyk' (/⁠pārsīg⁠/)\nEarly New Persian پَارْسِی (pārsī)\n▲\nArabic فَارِسِيّ (fārisiyy)influ.\nPersian فارسی\nInherited from Early New Persian پَارْسِی (pārsī), influenced by Arabic فَارِسِيّ (fārisiyy). By surface analysis, فارس (fārs /fârs, “Fars”) + ـی (-ī /-i, suffix forming adjectives). Compare Old Armenian պարսիկ (parsik), Sanskrit पारसिक (pārasika)."
